$ Excel: File -> Options -> Data

Change options related to → development/Data import and → development/Data/analysis[data analysis].

This feature is → https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/data-import-and-analysis-options-3ea52160-08bc-45ac-acd9-bc4a11bcc2a2[only available in Office 365 subscriptions].

{ Data options

   Make changes to the default layout of Pivot Tables (Edit Default Layout…)

   Disable undo for Pivot Tables with at least this number of data source rows (in thousands): nnn

   Prefer the Excel Data Model when creating PivotTables, QueryTables and Data Connections.

   Disable undo for large Data Model operations

   Disable undo for Data Model operations when the model is at least this large (in MB): nnn

   Enable Data Analysis add-ins Power Pivot and 3D Maps

   Disable automatic grouping of Date/Time columns in PivotTables

}
{ Show legacy data import wizards

  From … (Legacy)
    • Acess
    • Web
    • Text
    • Text
    • SQL Server
    • OData Data Feed
    • XML Data import
    • Microsoft Query

}
{ Automatic Data Conversion

  Remove leading zeros and convert to a number
  
  Keep first 15 digits of long numbers and display in scientific notation

  Convert digits surrounding the letter *E* to a number in scientific notation

  Convert continuous letters and numbers to a date
  -
 *Unsetting this option prevents the conversion of `march1` (but not `march 1`!) to a date*

  When loading a `.csv` file or similar file, notify me of any automatic data conversion

}
